# Astro site workflow

Site root is `rtikhonov.com/` (not the repo root). Run all Astro/wrangler commands from there.

## Preview

```bash
cd rtikhonov.com
astro dev --background   # or: npm run dev -- --host 127.0.0.1 --port 4321
```

If HMR looks stale (edits not reflected), kill the process on 4321 and restart. Prefer hard-refresh after image asset rewrites.

## Content “DB”

Prefer Astro content collections over inline arrays for growing lists (projects, etc.):

- Schema: `src/content.config.ts` with `glob` loader + Zod
- Entries: `src/content/<collection>/*.md`
- Dates for filtering: `z.coerce.date()` (ISO in frontmatter). Optional `dateEnd` for ranges
- Display formatting lives in `src/lib/` helpers — keep raw `Date` in data

## Deploy

When the user asks to deploy, follow `.cursor/rules/deploy.mdc` / the `deploy-site` skill (status → `npm run deploy` → URLs). Do not expand this section into a checklist.

`npm run deploy` runs docs checks, builds, then Wrangler with IPv4-first DNS (required on Node 24 + macOS). Push alone does not ship prod.

Do not run Astro or Wrangler from the repository root. There is no root `package.json`. Agent shells need nvm on PATH before npm.